<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-14T09:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-14T09:24:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860n.00/12: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-14T16:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            14, 1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:56
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>109. Noticeable improvement in general situation and believe no
                                immediate danger for our citizens or property. Have prepared list
                                names and addresses all Americans and perfected plans so far as is
                                possible for their evacuation if necessary.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>